      "message": "[Critical] Line 2067: This path can overwrite a previously declined re-invitation without requiring a fresh invitation. `addConversationRequest()` now allows a request when only a tombstone exists, but if `oldReq` exists and is declined, this code falls through and stores the new request regardless of whether the incoming request is actually newer. A replayed/stale invite can therefore undo a local decline and become acceptable again. Keep the existing declined request unless the incoming request is demonstrably newer, for example by comparing `received` or another request freshness marker before replacing it.\n```suggestion\n    if (oldReq !\u003d std::nullopt) {\n        JAMI_DEBUG(\"[Account {}] Received a request for a conversation already existing. \"\n                   \"Ignore. Declined: {}\",\n                   pimpl_-\u003eaccountId_,\n                   convId,\n                   oldReq-\u003edeclined);\n        if (!oldReq-\u003edeclined || req.received \u003c\u003d oldReq-\u003ereceived)\n            return;\n    }\n```",
